    shortDescription: "Brooks is a city in southeast Alberta, about 246 kilometres east of Calgary within the Eastern Irrigation District. Its 2021 census population was 14,451. The local economy centres on the JBS Foods beef-packing plant, one of Canada's largest, whose workforce has drawn people from around the world and made Brooks one of the country's most culturally diverse small cities. Surrounding farmland is fed by extensive EID irrigation canals, and Dinosaur Provincial Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, lies in the badlands to the northeast.",
