    shortDescription: "Drayton Valley is a town in Brazeau County, west-central Alberta, on the North Saskatchewan River about 169 kilometres southwest of Edmonton. Its 2021 census population was 7,235. The town grew rapidly after the 1953 discovery of the Pembina oil field, one of Canada's largest, which turned a small settlement into an oil-and-gas boomtown. Petroleum services still anchor the local economy, alongside forestry and newer clean-energy and bio-industrial ventures. Set in the transition between parkland and boreal forest near the foothills, Drayton Valley experiences long, cold winters.",
